rename.to: sftp: size of linked files not reported correctly

body:
The problem seems to be that the SFTP remote isn't returning the size of symlinks correctly...

On the server
```
$ ls -l
-rw-rw-r--  1 sftptest sftptest    6 Mar 16 11:35 hello.txt
lrwxrwxrwx  1 sftptest sftptest    9 Mar 16 11:35 link_to_hello.txt -> hello.txt
```

File is 6 bytes long

```
$ rclone cat TestSftp:link_to_hello.txt | wc
      1       1       6
```

However rclone thinks it is 9 bytes long.

```
$ rclone ls TestSftp:link_to_hello.txt
        9 link_to_hello.txt
```

rclone is likely reading the length of the link, on the server

```
$ readlink -n link_to_hello.txt  | wc
      0       1       9
```

I've fixed this here - please re-open if you have a problem - thanks!

https://beta.rclone.org/v1.39-254-gd1bb8efb/ (uploaded in 15-30 mins)
